 You\"\n| Alma Cogan\n| Tambourine (possibly)\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1964\n! scope=\"row\"| \"A World Without Love\"\n|[[Peter and Gordon]]\n| Composer\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1965\n! scope=\"row\"| \"You've Got To Hide Your Love Away\"\n| The Silkie\n| Rhythm guitar\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1966\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Got To Get You Into My Life\"\n| Cliff Bennett and the Rebel Rousers\n| Producer\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1966\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Mellow Yellow]]\"\n| [[Donovan]]\n| McCartney can be heard as a party reveler.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1967\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Smiley Smile]]''\n| [[The Beach Boys]]\n| Celery on \"[[Vegetables (song)|Vegetables]]\"\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1967\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[We Love You]]\"\n| [[The Rolling Stones]]\n| Backing vocals (with John Lennon)\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1968\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Tadpoles (album)|Tadpoles]]''\n| {{sort|BONZO DOG DOO DAH BAND|[[Bonzo Dog Doo Dah Band]]}}\n| Producer \u2014 the song \"I'm the Urban Spaceman\" (a #5 UK hit) was produced by McCartney and [[Gus Dudgeon]] under the collective pseudonym \"Apollo C. Vermouth\".\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1968\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Those Were the Days (song)|Those Were the Days]]\"\n| [[Mary Hopkin]]\n| Producer\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1968\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[James Taylor (album)|James Taylor]]''\n| {{sort|TAYLOR, JAMES|[[James Taylor]]}}\n| Bass on \"[[Carolina in My Mind]]\"\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1969\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Rosetta\" (non-album single)\n| {{sort|FOURMOST, THE|[[The Fourmost]]}}\n| Piano on \"Rosetta\"\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1969\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Magic Christian Music]]''\n| {{sort|BADFINGER|[[Badfinger]]}}\n| Composer and producer on \"Come and Get It\"; producer and piano on \"Rock of All Ages\"; and producer on \"Carry On Til Tomorrow\".\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1969\n! scope=\"row\"|